        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">What certifications does Webority hold for government work?</button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>CMMI Level 5, ISO 9001:2015, ISO 27001:2022, Startup India / DPIIT recognition, and GeM seller registration. Detailed certificates and validity dates are available to empanelment teams on request.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">How does Webority handle data security and DPDP Act 2023 compliance?</button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>We apply data classification at design time, encrypt at rest and in transit, restrict access by role with audit logging, and align our processing with Digital Personal Data Protection Act 2023 obligations. Sovereign-cloud and on-prem deployments are supported for data classified Sensitive or above.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">Does Webority offer post-deployment maintenance and support?</button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>Yes &mdash; SLA-bound managed services covering corrective, adaptive and preventive maintenance, with response and resolution times defined per severity. Our NOC and SOC functions are 24&times;7 ready.</p></div>
